quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
  29,15,"But We saved him together with the fellows of the Ark, and We made it a sign for<i class=""s"">(all people of) </i>all realms."
  29,16,"And Abraham—recall when he said to his people, “Worship Allah and be mindful of Him; that is better for you if you only knew."
  29,17,"Indeed, whatever you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>worship apart from Allah are nothing but idols, and you create fabrications. Those you worship apart from Allah possess no provision for you, so seek your provision with Allah and worship Him and thank Him; to Him <span class=""h"">you are returned<sup foot_note=""80786"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>.”"
  29,18,"And if you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>disbelieve, other communities before you have also disbelieved. And there is no responsibility upon the messenger except evident proclamation."
  29,19,"Have <span class=""h"">they<sup foot_note=""80787"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span><span class=""h"">not seen</span>how Allah starts creation and then restores it? This is indeed easy for Allah."
  29,20,"Say<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>, “Journey throughout the earth and look how He started creation.” Then Allah will bring about the next existence; Allah is indeed All-Powerful over everything.”"
  29,21,"He punishes whomever He wills and He grants mercy to whomever He wills, and to Him you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>are turned back."
  29,22,"And you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>can neither thwart<i class=""s"">(God) </i>on earth nor in heaven, and apart from Allah you have neither ally nor supporter."
  29,23,"And those who denied Allah’s signs and the meeting with Him—those have despaired of My{1}mercy, and for those is a painful punishment.",footnotes:1:A grammatical shift from 3rd person to 1st person.
